content.description: Start about 20 left of the starting ledge for The Fin. Climb the corner to the right of the big block of choss until under the thin roof. Place gear in a thin seam and pull directly over the overlap. Move left on the ledge and make the crux moves past 2 bolts. Continue up the steep face placing gear to a big spike of rock. Pull over the spike onto a belay ledge with a bolt anchor

climbs.name: Waiting For Arsenault
climbs.fa: Jon Garlough, Jim Dickson, Josh Corbett

content.description: The route was originally cleaned for the new local Steve Arsenault. Steve never did make it out, so the local crew "The Chinos" nabbed the route!    This climb starts on the left side of the Right Wall. A lone bolt 25' up marks the start. Climb up under a overlap and follow a left facing flake to its end. Make the crux moves and clip a bolt. Continue straight up the face placing gear and slinging natural threads in horizontals. Surmount a small juggy roof to a large ledge with a chain anchor.
content.protection: 1 bolt, Standard Rack, Long Runners, 2 Bolt Chain Anchor
content.location: All the way left on the Right Wall

content.description: Start 20 to the left of Clash City Rockers. Climb up past two bolts in the corner. Make an airy move out onto the protruding blade of rock and clip the third bolt. Make a tough mantle to gain a bolt anchor.

Start the same as Metal Blade. Climb up 10 to a ledge. Climb up the crack and follow the big arching flake left until it ends (#2-3 cams). Climb straight up to a shelf and then trend up and right on dirty terrain to the trees above.

Start at the far right end of the cliff. Climb up discontinuous cracks with distinct pods placing gear to the roof. Gain the horizontal on top of the roof and hand traverse left onto the overhang and climb straight up the face past a couple of ledges and clip a bolt. Make a funky move up to clip the bolt anchor.
content.location: Far right of the Right End

content.description: Start at a cleaned streak 25 left of Watch Owl. Climb up easy rock to a high first bolt with an optional gear placement down low. Continue up past three more bolts making a series of mantles to a large ledge. Run it out on easier slab to a bolt anchor.
content.protection: Bolts, Bolt Anchor, Optional gear low
content.location: Left side of the Right End

pathTokens: New Durham Area  (Longstack, Devil's Den, Rines Hill, etc.)

content.description: The Right End offers some quality climbing on quality rock. This is the largest section and tallest section of cliff. Most of the routes are mixed, so bring a small rack.
